text=Every WikiGroup can have a GroupHeader page that contains markup that should be included at the beginning of each page within the group.  This feature is primarily used for:께* adding a disclaimer or heading to all of the pages of a group* defining custom WikiStyles that may be used for all pages in a group* replacing the default headers and/or footers for pages in a group (using @@[=[[=]noheader]]@@ and @@[=[[=]nofooter]]@@ -- see SpecialMarkups)께GroupHeaders allow WikiUsers to create groups with custom headers and footers without having to coordinate with a WikiAdministrator.  For even more control, {{WikiAdministrator}}s can do PerGroupCustomizations as a {{LocalCustomization|s}}.께A wiki page within a group can suppress the default GroupHeader by using the @@[=[[=]nogroupheader]]@@ markup.께As of pmwiki-0.5.3, PmWiki now supports [=GroupFooter=] pages and the @@[=[[=]nogroupfooter]]@@ markup.께%trail%<<|PmWiki.DocumentationIndex|>>
